snippet.title: Johnny Depp performs with Hollywood Vampires in Portugal hours after Amber Heard accuses him of dome
snippet.description:
The Alice Through The Looking Glass star ignored Amber's shock allegations as he took to the stage in Lisbon 
Johnny Depp appeared to be in good spirits when he joined his band the Hollywood Vampires on stage on Friday night.
Hours earlier his estranged wife Amber Heard had accused him of domestic violence during a dramatic court hearing which took place five days after she filed for divorce.
Shrugging off the allegations, the actor took to the stage as the legendary group headlined the Rock in Rio Festival at Bela Vista Park in Lisbon, Portugal.
The seven-strong group wowed the crowds before Johnny posed for pictures with his famous bandmates, including Alice Cooper and Joe Perry.

snippet.title: AMBER SWEENEY | STRONG ENOUGH COVER | SONG CRUSH SUNDAY
snippet.description:
SONG CRUSH SUNDAY WITH AMBER SWEENEY 

Strong Enough by Sheryl Crow

I picked this song for a couple reasons. The first being that I get to go see Sheryl Crow for my birthday this week, and I wanted to pay homage to a woman who has been teaching me all these years and didn’t know it. The first time I heard Sheryl Crow, my mind was blown. It was the first time I understood how powerful words could be, and how a really good song also told a really good story. This song tells such a sad, but real story. When I was younger, I remember wanting people to be in my life so bad, that I would rather they pretend to be something to me, than to be true to themselves and leave. I’m sure some of that came from unresolved abandonment issues. I learned the hard way that it’s better to live authentically than to pretend. Pretending can build resentment over time, and that resentment makes a deeper cut than the tear way back at the beginning would have been. That’s at least what this song means to me. 

I’m playing my trusty Breedlove acoustic, and we filmed this at my home studio in Southwest Washington. 

In honor of giving credit where credit is due, here is the songwriter information for “Strong Enough”: 

“Strong Enough” written by -
Kevin Gilbert
Bill Bottrell
Sheryl Crow
Brian Macleod
David Baerwald
David Ricketts 

Thanks for watching and listening with your heart!

~Amber
